    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm doing the drywall in a small bathroom and im about to start the taping and mudding phase. can u walk me through the best way to do the seams so i dont end up with visible cracks or bumps later? thanks.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Start by applying a thin layer of joint compound directly over the seam tape, pressing it down gently to embed the mesh. For the first coat, feather the compound out wide to completely cover the seam and overlaps, letting it dry fully. Subsequent coats should be wider and feathered even further out, building up slowly to create a smooth, blended transition that disappears when sanded.",
      "source": "target",
