    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. what about the corners? i'm worried about the seams cracking where the walls meet or in the corners because of the humidity in a bathroom. how do i make sure those spots stay solid?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For inside corners, use a properly sized metal or fiberglass corner bead along the entire joint and embed it securely with your taping. In high-humidity areas like bathrooms, you can use a specialized flexible joint compound or a water-resistant mud for the finishing layers. Always ensure your mud is fully cured before extensive sanding, as rushing this step is a major cause of cracking.",
      "source": "target",
