    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok thanks. one more thing, i was looking at the wall before i started and noticed a couple of tiny little gaps and holes in the corners where the studs meet the plate. i'm assuming i should just fill those in with the mud while i'm doing the taping? or is there a better way to plug those deep holes so they don't cause issues later?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For small filler holes in the framing like those near the studs, lightweight joint compound is often sufficient when wedged firmly into the gaps. If any hole is deep or large, consider using a devilled patch or a small piece of drywall tape and mud over it to stabilize the area first. Ensure these patched areas are feathered out smoothly with your first coat of seam compound to keep the surface level with the rest of the wall.",
      "source": "target",
